<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08174b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08174b">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08174b"> 174(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> prisoners with limbs / broken cast into sea</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Over these prisoners a dispute arose; Raymond was for sparing their lives, Hervey de Montmorency for slaying. The eloquence of the latter prevailed. &ldquo;The citizens,&rdquo; says Giraldus, &ldquo;as men condemned, had their limbs broken and were cast headlong into the sea and so drowned.&rdquo; <small> Emily Lawless, <a name="ELIS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ELIS"><cite title="source">Ireland (Story of Nations series</cite></a> (192?) 85-6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
